Zapota Dos, ca. 20 km NW of Tortuguero village. On farm of Ronulfo Vargas. One-ha sample plot in tall forest on level ground, dominated by Pentaclethra macroloba (31% of basal area) Brosimum lactescens and Iriartea. Understory dominated by Protium pittieri, Socratea and Welfia.
